data.enText: the normal order and way in which you regularly do things

data.chText: 我们试着让婴儿按时进食和睡觉。
data.enText: We are trying to get the baby into a routine for feeding and sleeping.

data.chText: 让锻炼成为你日常生活的一部分。
data.enText: Make exercise a part of your daily routine .

data.chText: 我们定期清洗和修理机器。
data.enText: We clean and repair the machines as a matter of routine .
a situation in which life is boring because things are always done in the same way

data.chText: 她需要摆脱一下刻板的生活。
data.enText: She needed a break from routine .

data.chText: （演出中的）一套动作，一系列笑话（等）
data.enText: a series of movements, jokes, etc. that are part of a performance
a list of instructions that enable a computer to perform a particular task

data.chText: 常规的；例行公事的；日常的
data.enText: done or happening as a normal part of a particular job, situation or process

data.chText: 日常的询问；常规审问 / 检测
这个错误是在一次常规检查中发现的。
data.enText: The fault was discovered during a routine check.

data.chText: 平常的；正常的；毫不特别的
data.enText: not unusual or different in any way

data.chText: 他在一次普通手术中死于心脏病。
data.enText: He died of a heart attack during a routine operation.

data.chText: 这种工作很快就变得乏味无聊。
data.enText: This type of work rapidly becomes routine.

data.chText: 来访者在进入大楼时都要接受例行检查。
data.enText: Visitors are routinely checked as they enter the building.

simple_means.memory_skill: rout〔= route路〕+ ine 抽象名词 → 常走的道路 → 常规

means: (演出中的)一套动作，一系列笑话(等)

ex.zh: 晨间例事；平淡乏味的早晨

tr: an unvarying or habitual method or procedure
a set sequence of steps, part of larger computer program
a short theatrical performance that is part of a longer program
example: he did his act three times every evening
she had a catchy little routine
it was one of the best numbers he ever did

tr: found in the ordinary course of events
example: there's nothing quite like a real...train conductor to add color to a quotidian commute"- Anita Diaman

value.def: A routine is the usual series of things that you do at a particular time. A routine is also the practice of regularly doing things in a fixed order.

example.ex: The players had to change their daily routine and lifestyle...
example.tran: 这些运动员不得不改变他们的日常生活习惯和方式。

example.ex: They include the floor exercises as a regular part of their fitness routine...
example.tran: 他们把自由体操做为日常健身运动的固定环节。

example.ex: He checked up on you as a matter of routine.

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N n, adj N

value.def: You use routine to describe activities that are done as a normal part of a job or process.

example.tran: 一系列常规的医疗检查

example.ex: The operator has to be able to carry out routine maintenance of the machine.
example.tran: 操作员必须能对机器进行日常维护。

value.def: A routine situation, action, or event is one which seems completely ordinary, rather than interesting, exciting, or different.

example.ex: So many days are routine and uninteresting, especially in winter.
example.tran: 许多日子都过得平淡乏味，尤其是在冬天。

example.ex: ...this routine thriller about a CIA man and a KGB operative.
example.tran: 这部关于一个中情局特工和一个克格勃特务的平淡无奇的惊悚片

value.tran: 普通的;平常的;一般的;乏味的

value.def: You use routine to refer to a way of life that is uninteresting and ordinary, or hardly ever changes.

example.ex: Family holidays are meant to be a break from routine.
example.tran: 家庭假日就是从平淡的日常生活中解脱一下。

value.def: A routine is a computer program, or part of a program, that performs a specific function.
A routine is a short sequence of jokes, remarks, actions, or movements that forms part of a longer performance.

example.tran: 像马克思兄弟风格的搞笑套路

value.tran: （演出中的）一组笑话（或谈话等），一套动作
